contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:02.416 --> 03:05.853
Did you get it? Did
you get it on camera?

03:05.886 --> 03:07.488
No.

03:07.521 --> 03:08.822
Do you believe?

03:08.856 --> 03:12.926
I believe...I believe
it was a man in a monkey suit.

03:14.895 --> 03:17.931
There's no such thing as Bigfoot
and there's no such thing as

03:17.965 --> 03:22.403
Zombies, but that? That was no
man in a monkey suit!

03:38.686 --> 03:43.557
Now before you get your hopes
up, allow me to empty my cup.

03:43.591 --> 03:48.662
I am not a superhero.
I am not a superstar.

03:48.696 --> 03:53.367
I'm the guy you ask to help you
move. I'm the guy you meet at

03:53.401 --> 03:57.638
your local bar. And I am no
boyscout, all dressed up for

03:57.671 --> 04:02.510
show and go, oh no. In my little
head my Grandma's warning

04:02.543 --> 04:11.218
echoes from long ago. Michael,
remember: you reap what you sow.

04:11.251 --> 04:19.860
Mr. Thornton, I'm leaving now...
I have tickets to the theater.

04:22.463 --> 04:24.632
Michael?

04:24.665 --> 04:28.235
Go ahead, have a good night.

04:28.268 --> 04:32.840
And Michael? I realize this may
not be convenient but

04:32.873 --> 04:35.876
I'd like to ask for a raise.

04:36.877 --> 04:39.913
Before you say anything,
I'm very proficient with

04:39.947 --> 04:44.485
my duties and the clients
like me very much.

04:44.518 --> 04:47.287
Little people...

04:47.321 --> 04:50.257
You mean like- what, children?

04:50.290 --> 04:54.528
Yes, children. And I'm told,
dogs like me very much.

04:54.562 --> 04:56.897
You don't see
me asking for a raise.

04:56.930 --> 05:00.601
I hear in Europe you get a raise the 
very first day you start a job.

05:00.634 --> 05:03.904
Now why doesn't that
surprise me?

05:03.937 --> 05:06.273
What kind of raise
are we talking?

05:06.306 --> 05:10.310
I don't know, nothing grand or
obnoxious. Just something that

05:10.344 --> 05:14.281
says you appreciate me and my efforts
 and my many, many talents.

05:14.314 --> 05:17.284
Can't I just say I do appreciate
you and be done with it?

05:17.317 --> 05:21.689
No, it doesn't work that way,
Michael - You should know that.

05:21.722 --> 05:24.291
Besides, I thought you said you
were in a good mood today.

05:24.324 --> 05:29.997
Good moods. Yeah, I am in a good
mood. Go ahead, give yourself

05:30.030 --> 05:33.300
a raise and I'll sign it
on Monday morning.

05:33.333 --> 05:36.537
Well, and now you can now count
me among the many dogs and

05:36.570 --> 05:41.409
children that like you. And our
dear dear Mother would be

05:41.442 --> 05:46.313
very pleased with your
generosity.

05:46.346 --> 05:49.316
Enjoy your show. Sis.

05:49.349 --> 05:52.720
Have a pleasant weekend,
Mr. Thornton.

06:13.373 --> 06:17.344
Hey Bumble, it's the First day of summer. Can you believe it?

06:17.377 --> 06:20.347
I can believe it.
Longest day of the year.

06:20.380 --> 06:22.349
And a beautiful day it is.

06:22.382 --> 06:24.852
And already the crazies are out.

06:24.885 --> 06:26.754
You mean my ex-wife's
back in town?

06:27.921 --> 06:28.922
Please explain.

06:28.956 --> 06:30.958
You haven't heard
about the sightings?

06:30.991 --> 06:32.225
Go on.

06:32.259 --> 06:33.894
It seems Bigfoot is baacckk!

06:33.927 --> 06:35.195
You don't say?

06:35.228 --> 06:38.799
I do say. It seems Sasquatch is
alive and well. Multiple

06:38.832 --> 06:41.569
sightings in the last three
days. Although some say it

06:41.602 --> 06:44.371
looked like an escaped
ape or a gorilla.

06:44.404 --> 06:45.673
Is there a difference?

06:45.706 --> 06:49.777
Ah- beats me but one man says
his two dogs are missing.

06:49.810 --> 06:52.580
And he thinks Bigfoot did
it? What kind of dogs?

06:52.613 --> 06:55.549
Large ones, German
Shepherds. They were outside

06:55.583 --> 06:58.919
barking up a storm last
night. When one of them

06:58.952 --> 07:01.722
yelped - he went outside.
No dogs, Nein!

07:01.755 --> 07:03.791
Not even a trace of the dogs.

07:03.824 --> 07:06.860
Yeah, well it's been a long
winter. Perhaps he ate his dogs.

07:06.894 --> 07:08.261
Oh-

07:08.295 --> 07:10.030
Hey if you see two large German
Shepherd dogs goose-stepping it

07:10.063 --> 07:14.835
through the woods give us a
call. But if you see Bigfoot...

07:16.436 --> 07:18.405
Runnnn!!!

07:18.438 --> 07:19.840
And now back to some
summer music.

07:27.114 --> 07:28.415
Hello!

07:28.448 --> 07:31.118
Hi, uh- welcome to my home

07:31.151 --> 07:34.622
Oh this is quite lovely.

07:34.655 --> 07:39.993
Uh, where would you uh- like to
conduct the interview? I thought

07:40.027 --> 07:42.429
maybe the- the living room
would be most suitable.

07:42.462 --> 07:44.064
Oh this is just delightful.

07:44.097 --> 07:46.934
What if we have her seated in
front of the fireplace?

07:49.469 --> 07:51.772
Hello this is Phil Philbin, and
I have the remarkable

07:51.805 --> 07:54.942
opportunity of being in the
lovely home of famed author,

07:54.975 --> 07:59.780
Li Wei. Ms. Wei has agreed to
tell us her extraordinary

07:59.813 --> 08:04.985
happenstance on camera
in this exclusive interview.

08:05.018 --> 08:08.856
Li could you tell us your
experience exactly

08:08.889 --> 08:11.024
as it unfolded.

08:11.058 --> 08:17.030
Um- well we were uh- on our
usual thursday afternoon hike,

08:17.064 --> 08:22.035
and in no time we were very
much alone in the wilderness.

08:22.069 --> 08:28.709
There was a low growl from the
growth in front of me, and I-

08:28.742 --> 08:37.751
I know it was not from a small
animal and I was- I was frozen

08:37.784 --> 08:45.626
in my spot and then it appeared.

08:53.133 --> 08:58.105
and I just... I came to the
ravine, and I didn't know where

08:58.138 --> 09:06.179
to go. I was freefalling, just
50 feet straight down, and I

09:06.213 --> 09:11.652
don't know if I jumped or the
creature shoved me, but I was...

09:11.685 --> 09:13.320
I blacked out and-

09:14.321 --> 09:19.927
I- when I came to I was in a
creek and the smell was gone.

09:19.960 --> 09:24.297
so I surmised that the
creature had also vanished.

09:24.331 --> 09:30.638
Now was this when,
this happened?

09:45.018 --> 09:49.857
Yes, this- this is what I
got for my efforts.

09:49.890 --> 09:53.593
Well it- it could've
been much worse.

09:54.061 --> 09:57.998
Yes, I could have died.

09:58.031 --> 09:59.566
And then?

09:59.599 --> 10:03.036
And that's when I called you.

10:06.940 --> 10:08.842
What did you say?

10:08.876 --> 10:16.049
I- I said, beware the
woods. Be- beware the woods.

11:55.715 --> 11:57.150
Are you at the cabin?

11:57.184 --> 11:57.985
I am.

11:58.018 --> 11:59.152
Is she on her way?

11:59.186 --> 12:00.253
She is.

12:00.287 --> 12:02.089
Are you still going
through with it?

12:02.122 --> 12:02.990
Look Jerry...

12:05.258 --> 12:09.396
After Jessica died I thought
about her every single day.

12:09.429 --> 12:12.299
And I'll be the first to admit
my second marriage was a

12:12.332 --> 12:17.437
huge mistake... but
Sara...Sara's different.

12:17.470 --> 12:20.307
I think I'm very much in love.

12:20.340 --> 12:23.110
And you're not too
proud to admint it.

12:23.143 --> 12:24.144
Third time's the charm huh?

12:24.177 --> 12:24.878
You said it.

12:24.912 --> 12:26.313
Do you have a ring?

12:26.346 --> 12:27.480
Of course.

12:27.514 --> 12:29.149
I'll pop the question tonight.

12:29.182 --> 12:31.384
And she'll say yes.

12:31.418 --> 12:34.287
Are you on your way to another
happy hour at Rick's bar?

12:34.321 --> 12:37.825
No, I'm on my way to the cabin,
Your cabin. I've got some docs

12:37.858 --> 12:40.794
you have to sign off on.
They have to be delivered

12:40.828 --> 12:44.497
tomorrow morning, it's very,
very important to us.

12:44.531 --> 12:48.335
I thought we were
fine. After last week?

12:48.368 --> 12:50.037
Bad news good news.

12:50.070 --> 12:54.808
They started seizing our assets
but stopped abruptly. I moved

12:54.842 --> 12:57.310
all that I could without
waving a red flag to the IRS

12:57.344 --> 12:58.478
to come and arrest us.

12:58.511 --> 12:59.813
How bad is it?

12:59.847 --> 13:03.750
You mean how bad was it. On a
scale of 1-10 it was a 10+.

13:03.783 --> 13:06.186
We're lucky the Russian's
didn't bury us at the bottom

13:06.219 --> 13:12.125
of Castaic- Uh- Sorry, um- I
should'nt've said that.

13:12.159 --> 13:15.829
Look with a little maneuvering
and some timing, we'll survive

13:15.863 --> 13:17.464
this and be better than ever.

13:17.497 --> 13:18.866
That's good to hear.

13:18.899 --> 13:20.267
I don't know how you managed it.
You

13:20.300 --> 13:24.404
must be the luckiest guy I know.
Russians usually don't give up.

13:24.437 --> 13:25.939
Cut off the head.

13:25.973 --> 13:27.274
What's that?

13:27.975 --> 13:29.776
Mike-

13:29.809 --> 13:31.311
Yeah?

13:31.344 --> 13:34.447
Well I hate to ask but are
they uh- still looking for him?

13:34.481 --> 13:37.184
No they think he doesn't
want to be found.

13:37.217 --> 13:39.286
Ooh and we certainly don't
want him to be found.

13:39.319 --> 13:42.322
Not on the phone Jerry.

13:42.956 --> 13:45.859
Well how's uh-
how's Sara doing?

13:45.893 --> 13:47.794
She thinks he's
gone into hiding.

13:47.827 --> 13:51.131
Oh that's good, that's good.
See time heals all wounds.

13:51.164 --> 13:52.866
When will you be here?

13:52.900 --> 13:56.904
Well, traffic's a bitch.
Probably two or three hours.

13:56.937 --> 13:58.238
Sara?

13:58.271 --> 14:00.040
Within the hour.

14:00.073 --> 14:01.041
Well-

14:01.074 --> 14:04.011
say hello for me until
I can say it myself.

14:04.044 --> 14:05.312
I'll do that.

14:05.345 --> 14:08.581
Oh and Mike- Congratulations.

14:08.615 --> 14:10.517
Thanks.

14:59.232 --> 15:00.367
Michael?

15:00.400 --> 15:01.834
I'm here.

15:01.868 --> 15:02.936
Hey, I just wanted to let
you know I'm going to be

15:02.970 --> 15:05.038
a little late. Traffic sucks.

15:05.072 --> 15:06.273
So I've heard.

15:06.306 --> 15:09.642
I can't wait to see you.
Are you okay?

15:12.912 --> 15:16.449
If I lost- If I lost everything

15:17.384 --> 15:19.686
I'd love you even more.

15:21.388 --> 15:22.589
Hey what's happening?

15:22.622 --> 15:26.994
Nothing to worry about. Jerry
says we have it under control.

15:27.027 --> 15:30.097
I just want you to know
that no matter what,

15:30.130 --> 15:34.201
I will always love you. It
doesn' t matter what happens.

15:36.469 --> 15:37.404
I'll see you soon Michael.

15:39.006 --> 15:40.640
See you soon.

15:45.112 --> 15:49.216
You are one of the World's
Authorities on these creatures?

15:49.249 --> 15:54.054
Well I am the world's foremost
authority on the cryptid hominid

15:54.087 --> 15:59.226
or gigantophithecus canadensis
uh- or in lay terms;

15:59.259 --> 16:02.962
The Sasquatch and it's more
guttural cousin; Bigfoot-

16:02.996 --> 16:07.134
And we also must include the
Yeti in any discussions of

16:07.167 --> 16:11.038
scientific merit - And I am
slightly taken aback at the

16:11.071 --> 16:15.108
robust renewed interest in
these wonderful creatures.

16:15.142 --> 16:20.080
Lovely, lovely...And you say you
can imitate their sounds?

16:20.113 --> 16:25.085
Oh sounds? Oh- Of course. Uh-
and if I may say so, I am an

16:25.118 --> 16:26.953
expert in all three.

16:26.986 --> 16:30.590
Oh- Could you give us an actual
demonstration if needed?

16:30.623 --> 16:34.194
Demonstration? Oh, I'm
very flattered that you've

16:34.227 --> 16:39.632
asked. Um- I
will first do the Yeti.

16:49.042 --> 16:51.278
And now the Sasquatch.

16:56.216 --> 17:00.520
And now the 'piece de
resistance', the Bigfoot.

17:08.127 --> 17:13.665
Have you- Have you ever actually
seen one of these creatures?

17:13.700 --> 17:22.642
Oh- um- alas no. Uh- never.
But I do believe with my

17:22.675 --> 17:28.281
whole heart, that I will one day
walk hand in hand with them.

17:28.315 --> 17:30.049
In my next lifetime.

17:30.083 --> 17:32.485
I'm sure the feeling is mutual.

17:32.519 --> 17:35.322
I'm just saying, any animal
that is teased long enough

17:35.355 --> 17:36.756
will attack you.

17:36.789 --> 17:39.092
What about a shark, a shark is
going to attack you whether

17:39.126 --> 17:40.560
you tease it or not.

17:40.593 --> 17:42.362
I'm not talking about a shark,
I'm talking about a land animal.

17:42.395 --> 17:45.165
Is a shark considered to be an
animal? I know it's a fish

17:45.198 --> 17:46.199
but is it an animal?

17:46.233 --> 17:46.866
I think so.

17:46.899 --> 17:47.934
Yeah. I think so too.

17:47.967 --> 17:49.702
So what's the difference
between a Yeti,

17:49.736 --> 17:51.504
a Sasquatch, and Bigfoot?

17:51.538 --> 17:55.242
Alright so a Yeti is like the
abominable snow man. He's all

17:55.275 --> 17:56.409
white and he lives in the snow.

17:56.443 --> 17:57.744
Agreed.

17:57.777 --> 18:00.213
A Sasquatch makes its'
home in the Redwoods.

18:00.247 --> 18:01.314
Also agreed.

18:01.348 --> 18:02.415
But Bigfoot...

18:02.449 --> 18:04.083
Bigfoot can live anywhere.

18:04.117 --> 18:06.219
Give the lady a prize.

18:06.253 --> 18:07.520
Why are we here again?

18:07.554 --> 18:10.390
Two hundred dollars a
pound for morel mushrooms.

18:10.423 --> 18:11.524
And where are these fungi?

18:11.558 --> 18:12.525
There's a fungus among us...

18:12.559 --> 18:13.793
It should be just over this way.

18:19.399 --> 18:22.335
Oh my God. What is that?

18:29.509 --> 18:31.611
Well is it human or animal?

18:31.644 --> 18:33.513
I guess now we know
why they call it Bigfoot.

19:10.583 --> 19:13.253
Good morning. Coffee?

19:14.621 --> 19:17.690
Sorry I'm not a stalker I just
see you in this coffee shop

19:17.724 --> 19:21.528
all the time and I wanted
to say hi. I'm Sara.

19:28.167 --> 19:30.503
To you whenever you arrive.

20:24.357 --> 20:25.392
Michael?

20:47.013 --> 20:48.315
Cheers.

20:59.659 --> 21:02.429
Well it's about time.

21:07.600 --> 21:09.669
What happened?

21:13.640 --> 21:14.541
Why?

21:30.523 --> 21:31.524
Sara?

21:33.893 --> 21:40.066
Michael...

22:11.664 --> 22:13.400
Sara!

23:55.868 --> 23:56.903
What nationality are you?

23:56.936 --> 23:58.638
I'm a purebred mutt.

23:59.872 --> 24:03.543
I'm Russian. Purebred Russian

24:03.576 --> 24:05.444
Where's your accent?

24:05.478 --> 24:08.648
My father inssisted that I go to
only the best schools, and

24:08.681 --> 24:11.450
that meant you know my accent
was the first thing to go.

24:13.753 --> 24:19.091
I think you might like my dad. I
think he might like you too.

24:19.125 --> 24:24.997
You guys are both... Well I
mean you- you heard the rumors.

24:26.599 --> 24:29.035
Guys like me don't get here
without doing things-

24:29.068 --> 24:31.804
a bit differently.

24:31.838 --> 24:36.776
My mom used to say- A man
can never truly find himself

24:36.809 --> 24:39.646
until he is reduced
to his most basic self.

24:39.679 --> 24:41.213
And what does that mean?

24:41.247 --> 24:46.152
I don't know but it seemed like
the appropriate time to say it.

24:50.723 --> 24:53.092
I want you to meet my family.

24:53.125 --> 24:54.994
That's a big step isn't it.

24:55.027 --> 24:57.163
If you're scared its a big step.

24:57.196 --> 25:01.901
If you're a big strong man I
think you can handle it.

25:01.934 --> 25:03.903
Are you a big
strong man Michael.

25:03.936 --> 25:06.939
I have my moments.

27:02.154 --> 27:04.123
Sara!

27:27.814 --> 27:31.317
Hi, this is Michael. With any
luck I'm out having a

27:31.350 --> 27:35.021
great time. Leave your sunny
message after the tone.

27:36.322 --> 27:43.763
Michael, it's your sis. I
realize that you're in the

27:43.796 --> 27:48.400
throes of impending marital
bliss, but I just wanted to call

27:48.434 --> 27:53.105
and wish you every happiness.
I'm certain that Sara will

27:53.139 --> 27:58.144
give you everything that you
deserve. And Michael...

27:58.177 --> 28:02.381
Even if there's a couple of
bumps along the road,

28:02.414 --> 28:05.417
I have no doubt that you
two can smooth it over.

28:07.186 --> 28:13.826
Well, I guess that's it for now
dear brother. I love you. Ta ta.

28:26.272 --> 28:27.406
I'm getting dizzy Michael.

28:29.375 --> 28:34.146
Will you catch me if I fall?
Because I'm falling Michael.

28:34.180 --> 28:36.115
I'm falling for you!

28:44.791 --> 28:46.125
Sara!

29:04.276 --> 29:06.278
Sara!

29:10.116 --> 29:13.219
You can survive
days without food.

29:13.252 --> 29:15.487
But you cannot survive
without water.

29:15.521 --> 29:17.323
If you wouldn't have forgotten
the water we would have

29:17.356 --> 29:18.858
no problems right now.

29:18.891 --> 29:22.094
No problems? You don't even know where we are. Who doesn't

29:22.128 --> 29:24.330
bring a map or a cell phone?

29:24.363 --> 29:27.266
Why would I want some
kind of electronic device

29:27.299 --> 29:30.236
out here amongst all
this natural beauty?

29:30.269 --> 29:32.438
It's the antithesis of why
we came out here.

29:32.471 --> 29:35.975
And I'm just realizing how
truly clueless you really are.

29:36.008 --> 29:39.045
First rule of hiking, know where
you are at all times.

29:39.078 --> 29:40.312
Well where's your cell phone?

29:40.346 --> 29:42.815
In the car which we
can't find because of you.

29:42.849 --> 29:45.317
Why did I even agree to
this? I don't like hiking.

29:45.351 --> 29:48.754
Hiking is fine as long as you
remember the water.

29:48.787 --> 29:50.122
You're an idiot.

29:50.156 --> 29:52.091
You know what, name calling is
going to do nothing to help us.

29:52.124 --> 29:53.125
Idiot.

29:54.393 --> 29:58.130
Alright alright, I'll make you a
deal. If you get us out of here,

29:58.164 --> 29:59.598
I'll stop calling you names.

29:59.631 --> 30:06.338
I highly doubt that- but sure.
You've got yourself a deal.

30:06.372 --> 30:08.374
Mind if we keep moving?

30:11.377 --> 30:13.812
Look lights.

30:13.846 --> 30:15.547
Is that a cabin?

30:15.581 --> 30:19.518
Yeah I think it is. I can
taste the water from here.

30:19.551 --> 30:22.354
I take it back. No deal.
You really are an idiot.

30:22.388 --> 30:25.791
What is that awful smell?

30:25.824 --> 30:27.927
It's got to be a
dead animal around here.

30:27.960 --> 30:30.429
I think I'm going to be sick.

30:33.065 --> 30:34.400
What is that?

30:36.368 --> 30:37.403
What is that?

30:41.908 --> 30:43.075
Help me.

30:44.176 --> 30:45.511
Help me!

32:53.172 --> 32:55.974
Where are we going
with all this Michael.

32:58.310 --> 33:02.714
I've fallen in love with you.
I didn't mean for it to happen,

33:02.748 --> 33:07.986
It just did. What
about you Michael.

33:12.491 --> 33:13.692
I know you've been married.

33:13.725 --> 33:15.261
Twice.

33:19.631 --> 33:21.633
Care to try for three?

33:24.136 --> 33:25.671
Daddy wants to meet you.

33:25.704 --> 33:27.173
Why?

33:27.206 --> 33:29.475
Because I've told him about you.

33:29.508 --> 33:32.678
He's my father Michael.
He's very protective

33:32.711 --> 33:36.348
of his little girl. Meeting you
would give him some comfort.

33:36.382 --> 33:38.617
You'd want to protect me right?

33:42.788 --> 33:46.024
It's time Michael. You can't
hide from him forever.

33:48.460 --> 33:50.462
Buck up Bucko

34:01.373 --> 34:02.241
Name?

34:02.274 --> 34:04.210
Michael Thornton.

34:04.243 --> 34:06.245
You're on the list Mr. Thornton.

34:45.284 --> 34:48.687
Michael, finally, hurry.
Daddy's waiting.

34:54.426 --> 34:58.364
Daddy, This is Michael.

34:58.397 --> 35:01.099
So this is the bastard who
wants to steal my daughter?

35:01.133 --> 35:04.636
Hey, don't intimidate him.
He's not like the others.

35:09.541 --> 35:12.144
